\begin{abstract}
This document presents the unified theory obtained by embedding the
Dualitas calculus into a physically meaningful dynamical kernel.
The result is a complete structural framework in which rewrite systems,
symbolic dynamics, category theory, homotopy theory, spectral theory,
and renormalization group flow coexist within a single generative
substrate. The kernel provides the canonical $\varphi$-operator that
drives universe evolution, while Dualatalis supplies the algebraic,
topological, and logical infrastructure. Together they form a unified
theory of structure capable of generating, classifying, and analyzing
emergent universes across physics, computation, and mathematics.
\end{abstract}

