programming system in which computation is expressed as symbolic
rewriting, categorical structure, and dynamical evolution. Programs are
rewrite systems, data are words in a free monoid, and execution is the
iteration of a canonical evolution operator $\varphi$. The language
integrates algebraic, topological, homotopical, and spectral semantics,
providing a unified computational substrate for mathematics, physics,
and emergent structure. Dualatalis is not a language that performs
mathematics; it is a language in which mathematics itself is the
computational model.
