\section{Overview}

The Dualatalis language is built on the principle that computation and
mathematics share a common foundation: symbolic rewriting. In this
language:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Programs} are rewrite systems.
  \item \textbf{Data} are words in a free monoid.
  \item \textbf{Functions} are monoid endomorphisms.
  \item \textbf{Types} are algebraic, topological, or categorical structures.
  \item \textbf{Execution} is the iteration of a $\varphi$-operator.
  \item \textbf{Semantics} are given by category theory, topos theory,
        homotopy theory, and spectral analysis.
\end{itemize}

The language is designed to express structural computation: the
generation, transformation, and analysis of symbolic universes.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\section{Philosophy}

\subsection{Mathematics as Computation}

In Dualatalis, computation is not an approximation of mathematics; it is
mathematics. Every program is a mathematical object, and every execution
step is a mathematical transformation.

\subsection{Local Rules, Global Structure}

Programs consist of local growth and repair rules. Global behavior
emerges from the iteration of these rules, mirroring the structure of
Dualitas and the kernel.

\subsection{Universes as Data}

A program does not manipulate numbers or arrays; it manipulates
universes. A universe is a word, and its evolution is a rewrite orbit.

\subsection{Semantic Richness}

The language supports multiple semantic layers:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Operational semantics}: rewrite dynamics.
  \item \textbf{Denotational semantics}: functorial and topos semantics.
  \item \textbf{Homotopy semantics}: rewrite paths and homotopy colimits.
  \item \textbf{Spectral semantics}: Koopman operator and eigenmodes.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Universality}

The language is Turing-complete and capable of expressing universal
structure formation.

