%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\section{Syntax}

The syntax of the Dualatalis language is designed to be minimal,
structural, and mathematically transparent. Every construct corresponds
directly to an element of the Dualatalis calculus.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Alphabet Declarations}

An alphabet introduces the set of symbols used in the program:

\begin{verbatim}
alphabet {A, B, C}
\end{verbatim}

Formally, this defines:


\[
  \Sigma = \{A, B, C\}.
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Word Literals}

Words are written as sequences of symbols:

\begin{verbatim}
word w = A B A C
\end{verbatim}

This corresponds to:


\[
  w = ABAC.
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Rule Definitions}

A rule maps each symbol to a word:

\begin{verbatim}
rule grow {
  A -> AB
  B -> A
  C -> BC
}
\end{verbatim}

Formally:


\[
  r_{\mathrm{g}} : \Sigma \to \Sigma^{*}.
\]



Repair rules are defined similarly:

\begin{verbatim}
rule repair {
  A -> A
  B -> B
  C -> C
}
\end{verbatim}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Evolution Operator Definition}

The evolution operator $\varphi$ is defined by composing growth and
repair rules:

\begin{verbatim}
phi = repair ∘ grow
\end{verbatim}

If no repair rule is present:

\begin{verbatim}
phi = grow
\end{verbatim}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Universe Blocks}

A universe is defined by specifying an alphabet, an initial word, and an
evolution operator:

\begin{verbatim}
universe U {
  alphabet {A, B}
  initial A
  rule grow {
    A -> AB
    B -> A
  }
  phi = grow
}
\end{verbatim}

This corresponds to the vanfold:


\[
  V = (\Sigma, w_0).
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Iteration Constructs}

Execution is expressed by iterating $\varphi$:

\begin{verbatim}
iterate U.phi for 20
\end{verbatim}

This computes:


\[
  w_{t+1} = \varphi(w_t), \qquad 0 \le t < 20.
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Observables}

Observables are functions on universes:

\begin{verbatim}
observable length(w) = |w|
observable count(w, A) = #A in w
\end{verbatim}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Measurement}

To evaluate an observable during execution:

\begin{verbatim}
measure length during iterate U.phi for 50
\end{verbatim}

