The language infers structural types automatically:

\begin{itemize}
  \item If $\varphi(w^{*}) = w^{*}$, infer \texttt{FixedPoint}.
  \item If $\varphi^{p}(w) = w$, infer \texttt{Periodic}.
  \item If $h(\varphi) = 0$ and $\rho = 1$, infer \texttt{Quasiperiodic}.
  \item If $h(\varphi) > 0$, infer \texttt{Chaotic}.
  \item If $\varphi$ simulates a Turing machine, infer \texttt{Universal}.
\end{itemize}

