\section{Operational Semantics}

The operational semantics of the Dualatalis language define how programs
execute. Execution is symbolic rewriting: each step applies the
evolution operator $\varphi$ to a universe configuration.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Evaluation Context}

A program state consists of:


\[
  (\Sigma, w, r_{\mathrm{g}}, r_{\mathrm{r}}, \varphi, t),
\]


where:
\begin{itemize}
  \item $\Sigma$ is the alphabet,
  \item $w$ is the current word (universe configuration),
  \item $r_{\mathrm{g}}$ is the growth rule,
  \item $r_{\mathrm{r}}$ is the repair rule,
  \item $\varphi$ is the evolution operator,
  \item $t$ is the current time step.
\end{itemize}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Symbol Rewriting}

A rule $r$ rewrites a symbol $s$ by:


\[
  r(s) = u \in \Sigma^{*}.
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Word Rewriting}

A rule extends homomorphically:


\[
  r(s_1 s_2 \dots s_n) = r(s_1) r(s_2) \dots r(s_n).
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Growth Semantics}

The growth rule $r_{\mathrm{g}}$ is applied first:


\[
  w' = r_{\mathrm{g}}(w).
\]



This corresponds to the forward kernel update.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Repair Semantics}

If a repair rule is defined, it is applied next:


\[
  w'' = r_{\mathrm{r}}(w').
\]



This enforces invariants such as:
\begin{itemize}
  \item normalization,
  \item conservation laws,
  \item geometric constraints,
  \item stability corrections.
\end{itemize}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Evolution Semantics}

The evolution operator is:


\[
  \varphi(w) =
  \begin{cases}
    r_{\mathrm{r}}(r_{\mathrm{g}}(w)), & r_{\mathrm{r}} \text{ exists},\\
    r_{\mathrm{g}}(w), & \text{otherwise}.
  \end{cases}
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Iteration Semantics}

The iteration construct:
\begin{verbatim}
iterate U.phi for N
\end{verbatim}
executes:


\[
  w_{t+1} = \varphi(w_t), \qquad 0 \le t < N.
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Deterministic Evolution}

If $r_{\mathrm{g}}$ and $r_{\mathrm{r}}$ are deterministic, then $\varphi$
is deterministic:


\[
  w_{t+1} = \varphi(w_t)
\]


is uniquely defined.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Stochastic Evolution}

A stochastic rule is defined as:


\[
  r(s) = u_i \quad \text{with probability } p_i.
\]



The evolution operator becomes a Markov process:


\[
  \mathbb{P}(w_{t+1} = v \mid w_t = w)
  = \mathbb{P}(\varphi(w) = v).
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Observables During Execution}

Given an observable $f : \Sigma^{*} \to \mathbb{C}$, the construct:
\begin{verbatim}
measure f during iterate U.phi for N
\end{verbatim}
computes:


\[
  f(w_t) \quad \text{for } 0 \le t \le N.
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Structural Queries}

Structural queries evaluate properties of the evolution operator:

\begin{verbatim}
fixed_points of U
cycles of U
entropy of U
spectrum of U
homotopy of U
\end{verbatim}

These correspond to:


\[
  \varphi(w^{*}) = w^{*}, \qquad
  \varphi^{p}(w) = w, \qquad
  h(\varphi), \qquad
  \sigma(U_{\varphi}), \qquad
  \Pi_{1}(G_{\varphi}).
\]



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Universe Execution Semantics}

A universe executes by repeatedly applying $\varphi$:


\[
  U(t) = \varphi^{t}(w_0).
\]



The full execution trace is:


\[
  \{ w_0, w_1, w_2, \dots, w_N \}.
\]

