\subsection{Interpreter Architecture}

A Dualatalis interpreter consists of the following components:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Parser} — reads alphabet, rules, universes, and constructs.
  \item \textbf{Symbol Table} — stores $\Sigma$, rules, and $\varphi$.
  \item \textbf{Rewrite Engine} — applies $r_{\mathrm{g}}$ and $r_{\mathrm{r}}$.
  \item \textbf{Execution Engine} — iterates $\varphi$.
  \item \textbf{Observer} — evaluates observables and structural queries.
  \item \textbf{Analyzer} — computes entropy, spectrum, homotopy, RG flow.
\end{itemize}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Rewrite Engine}

The rewrite engine applies rules homomorphically:



\[
  r(s_1 s_2 \dots s_n) = r(s_1) r(s_2) \dots r(s_n).
\]



Implementation strategies:

\begin{itemize}
  \item direct string concatenation,
  \item rope-based data structures,
  \item tree-based representations,
  \item GPU-accelerated parallel rewriting.
\end{itemize}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Execution Engine}

The execution engine performs:



\[
  w_{t+1} = \varphi(w_t).
\]



Execution loop:

\begin{verbatim}
for t in 0..N:
    w = phi(w)
    observe(w)
\end{verbatim}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Optimization Strategies}

\paragraph{Memoization.}
Cache results of $r(s)$ and $r(w)$ for repeated patterns.

\paragraph{Pattern Compression.}
Use run-length encoding or grammar-based compression for large words.

\paragraph{Sparse Representation.}
For universes with localized activity, store only active regions.

\paragraph{Incremental Repair.}
Apply $r_{\mathrm{r}}$ only where invariants are violated.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Parallel Rewrite Execution}

Rewrite rules are local and independent:



\[
  r(s_i) \text{ does not depend on } s_j \text{ for } i \neq j.
\]



Thus rewriting is embarrassingly parallel.

Parallel strategies:

\begin{itemize}
  \item CPU thread-per-symbol,
  \item GPU kernel-per-symbol,
  \item SIMD vectorized rewriting,
  \item distributed rewriting across nodes.
\end{itemize}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Stochastic Execution Engine}

For stochastic rules:



\[
  r(s) = u_i \quad \text{with probability } p_i,
\]



the interpreter must:

\begin{itemize}
  \item sample from the distribution,
  \item propagate randomness through $\varphi$,
  \item support Monte Carlo execution,
  \item compute ensemble averages of observables.
\end{itemize}

